    <!-- OVERVIEW ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-blue" style="--i:0" id="overview">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">📋</div>
        <div class="section-title">Overview</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <div class="hi-icon">💡</div>
          <p><strong>The short version:</strong> My Folder stores all your files and data 100% on your device. We collect nothing. We transmit nothing. No account is required.</p>
        </div>
        <p>My Folder is a personal file manager for iPhone and iPad. This privacy policy explains what information the app accesses, how it is used, and your rights as a user.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S1 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-rose" style="--i:1" id="s1">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">1</div>
        <div class="section-title">Information We Collect</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p><strong>We do not collect any personal information.</strong></p>
        <p>My Folder does not:</p>
        <ul class="policy-list">
          <li>Require an account or registration</li>
          <li>Collect your name, email address, or any personal identifiers</li>
          <li>Track your location</li>
          <li>Access your contacts or calendar</li>
          <li>Connect to any server or third-party service</li>
          <li>Contain any analytics, crash reporting, or advertising SDKs</li>
          <li>Transmit any data to the developer or any third party</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S2 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-blue" style="--i:2" id="s2">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">2</div>
        <div class="section-title">Data Stored on Your Device</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>All data created and managed by My Folder is stored exclusively on your device in the app's private sandbox:</p>
        <div class="data-table-wrap">
          <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Data</th>
                <th>Where Stored</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Your files (PDFs, images, documents)</td>
                <td>Device local storage (Documents directory)</td>
                <td>Core app function — file management</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Folder structure and names</td>
                <td>SwiftData (on-device SQLite)</td>
                <td>Organising your files</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Document metadata (name, date, priority)</td>
                <td>SwiftData (on-device SQLite)</td>
                <td>File list display and sorting</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>App-level document passwords</td>
                <td>SwiftData — <code>PBKDF2-SHA256</code> hash + salt only</td>
                <td>Per-document security</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Temporary import files</td>
                <td>App Group: <code>group.com.BJ.MyFolder</code></td>
                <td>Receiving files from the Share Extension</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div class="note">
          🔐 All files are stored with <strong>iOS Full File Protection</strong> (<code>NSFileProtectionComplete</code>), encrypted by iOS when the device is locked and inaccessible to any other app.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S3 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-amber" style="--i:3" id="s3">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">3</div>
        <div class="section-title">Device Permissions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>My Folder requests the following iOS permissions only when you use the relevant features:</p>
        <div class="perm-grid">

          <div class="perm-card cam">
            <div class="perm-icon">📷</div>
            <div class="perm-name">Camera</div>
            <p class="perm-desc">Used only when you tap <strong>Scan</strong> to capture a physical document. Photos are immediately converted to PDF and saved locally. No images are sent anywhere.</p>
            <div class="perm-usage">"My Folder uses the camera to scan documents and convert them to PDF."</div>
          </div>

          <div class="perm-card photo">
            <div class="perm-icon">🖼️</div>
            <div class="perm-name">Photo Library</div>
            <p class="perm-desc">Used when you choose to import a photo. Selected photos are copied into the app's private storage and not accessed again. Also used when exporting a file back to Photos.</p>
            <div class="perm-usage">"My Folder needs access to your photos to import images into your folders."</div>
          </div>

          <div class="perm-card faceid">
            <div class="perm-icon">🔐</div>
            <div class="perm-name">Face ID / Touch ID</div>
            <p class="perm-desc">Requested on every app launch to protect your files. Authentication is performed entirely by iOS — My Folder never sees your biometric data.</p>
            <div class="perm-usage">"My Folder uses Face ID to securely protect your folders so only you can access them."</div>
          </div>

          <div class="perm-card mic">
            <div class="perm-icon">🎙️</div>
            <div class="perm-name">Microphone (Indirect)</div>
            <p class="perm-desc">The iOS document scanner (<code>VNDocumentCameraViewController</code>) may trigger a microphone prompt on some system versions. My Folder does not use the microphone and records no audio.</p>
            <div class="perm-usage">System-triggered only. Not used by My Folder directly.</div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S4 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-teal" style="--i:4" id="s4">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">4</div>
        <div class="section-title">Share Extension</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>My Folder includes a Share Extension (<strong>"Save to My Folder"</strong>) that appears in the iOS share sheet of other apps.</p>
        <ul class="policy-list check">
          <li>Files you share are <strong>copied</strong> into a temporary folder in the My Folder App Group container, stored entirely on your device.</li>
          <li>When you next open My Folder, those files are moved into your chosen folder.</li>
          <li>The Share Extension <strong>cannot</strong> access any files or data beyond those you explicitly share.</li>
          <li>No data is sent to any server. Everything stays on your device.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S5 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-violet" style="--i:5" id="s5">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">5</div>
        <div class="section-title">Password Security</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>My Folder supports two levels of password protection:</p>
        <div class="pwd-grid">
          <div class="pwd-card app">
            <div class="pwd-card-title">🔑 App-Level Document Passwords</div>
            <p>Stored using <strong>PBKDF2-SHA256</strong> with a unique 32-byte random salt and 100,000 iterations. Only the derived hash and salt are stored — your plain-text password is never saved anywhere.</p>
            <span class="tag violet">PBKDF2-SHA256</span>
            <span class="tag blue">100,000 iterations</span>
          </div>
          <div class="pwd-card pdf">
            <div class="pwd-card-title">📄 Native PDF Passwords</div>
            <p>Applied directly to the PDF file using <strong>AES-256 encryption</strong> via Apple's <code>CGPDFContext</code> framework. The password lives inside the encrypted PDF file itself, consistent with the PDF standard.</p>
            <span class="tag green">AES-256</span>
            <span class="tag green">PDF Standard</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="note">The developer has no access to your passwords. If you forget your password, it cannot be recovered.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S6 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-rose" style="--i:6" id="s6">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">6</div>
        <div class="section-title">Data Sharing</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <div class="hi-icon">🚫</div>
          <p>We do not share your data with anyone — because we do not have your data.</p>
        </div>
        <p>My Folder does not use any third-party frameworks, SDKs, advertising networks, analytics services, or cloud platforms. There is no backend server.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S7 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-amber" style="--i:7" id="s7">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">7</div>
        <div class="section-title">Data Retention &amp; Deletion</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>All data is stored on your device under your full control.</p>
        <ul class="policy-list dot">
          <li><strong>Deleting a document</strong> in the app permanently removes the file from your device.</li>
          <li><strong>Deleting a folder</strong> permanently removes all documents inside it.</li>
          <li><strong>Deleting the app</strong> removes all app data, files, and settings from your device (standard iOS behaviour).</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:12px">The developer retains no copies of your data.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S8 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-teal" style="--i:8" id="s8">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">8</div>
        <div class="section-title">Children's Privacy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>My Folder does not collect any personal information from any user, including children. The app complies with the <strong>Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)</strong> and equivalent regulations. Its App Store age rating is <strong>4+</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S9 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-green" style="--i:9" id="s9">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">9</div>
        <div class="section-title">Security</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your information:</p>
        <div class="security-grid">
          <div class="sec-badge">
            <div class="sec-badge-icon">🔒</div>
            <div class="sec-badge-text">
              <strong>iOS Full File Protection</strong>
              <span>Files encrypted when device is locked</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sec-badge">
            <div class="sec-badge-icon">👁</div>
            <div class="sec-badge-text">
              <strong>Biometric Lock</strong>
              <span>Face ID / Touch ID prevents unauthorised access</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sec-badge">
            <div class="sec-badge-icon">🔑</div>
            <div class="sec-badge-text">
              <strong>PBKDF2-SHA256</strong>
              <span>Industry-standard password hashing</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sec-badge">
            <div class="sec-badge-icon">🌐</div>
            <div class="sec-badge-text">
              <strong>Zero Network Access</strong>
              <span>No data in transit to intercept</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S10 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-blue" style="--i:10" id="s10">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">10</div>
        <div class="section-title">Your Rights</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>Since My Folder stores all data locally on your device and we collect no personal information:</p>
        <div class="rights-grid">
          <div class="right-card">
            <div class="r-icon">👁️</div>
            <div class="r-title">Access</div>
            <div class="r-desc">All your data is visible and accessible within the app at all times.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="right-card">
            <div class="r-icon">✏️</div>
            <div class="r-title">Correction</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Rename, edit, or replace any file at any time.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="right-card">
            <div class="r-icon">🗑️</div>
            <div class="r-title">Deletion</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Delete any file or folder. Deleting the app removes all data.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="right-card">
            <div class="r-icon">📤</div>
            <div class="r-title">Export</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Share any file to another app via the iOS share sheet at any time.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:16px">If you are a resident of the European Union or California and have additional privacy questions, please contact us at the email below — though please note that we have no personal data about you to disclose, correct, or delete.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- S11 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="section s-ink" style="--i:11" id="s11">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">11</div>
        <div class="section-title">Changes to This Policy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <p>If we make material changes to this privacy policy, the updated version will be published at the URL listed at the top of this document and the "Effective Date" will be updated. Continued use of the app after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the new policy.</p>
      </div>
